{"search_data": "Central Spouse Now Eligible for Pension Under Atal Pension YojanaIn case of death of both subscriber and spouse, the nominee will be entitled to receive the pension wealth, as accumulated till age of 60 years of the subscriber.The spouse will now be able to continue the contribution to the plan for remaining period and receive same pension benefits after the subscriber would have completed 60 years.In exceptional circumstances, that is, in the event of the death of beneficiary or specified illness, as mentioned in the PFRDA (Exit and withdrawals under the National Pension System) Regulations, 2015, before the age of 60 years, the accumulated pension wealth till date would be given to the nominee or the subscriber as the case may be.Read more about the Atal Pension Yojana  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}